  "text": "Collins and Male generalized in [CITATION_1] the result above to arbitrary unitarily invariant random matrices, by dropping the GUE hypothesis and asking that individual matrices X . Their result will be crucial to the present paper, since it will allow us to prove that the extremal eigenvalues have indeed the behavior suggested by the convergence in distribution (i.e. they converge to the extrema of the support of the limiting eigenvalue distribution, in the single matrix case k = 1).",
